ques.p: To ask the Secretary of State for Justice how many unpaid work appointments have been cancelled since January, broken down by probation area. [Official Report, 18 November 2007, Vol. 468, c. 3MC.]

reply.p: Across all probation areas a total of 29,852 work appointments were cancelled between 1 January 2007 and 30 June 2007. This compares with 644,697 appointments which were kept, which is a cancellation rate of 4.6 per cent.
